.TH UUENCODE 1
.SH NAME
uuencode, uudecode \- encode/decode a file as printable ASCII
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B uuencode
[
.I input
]
.PP
.B uudecode
[
.I input
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Uuencode
and
.I uudecode
are filters used to transmit files over transmission media
that do not support other than simple ASCII data.
.PP
.I Uuencode
converts a file to a purely ASCII-based representation.
.PP
.I Uudecode
reads a file produced by
.IR uuencode ,
ignoring any leading and trailing lines that are not part of the encoding,
and
emits the original file on standard output,
also writing its name to standard error.
.SH EXAMPLES
Encode a
.I dis
file
.I limbo.dis
so that it can be included in a mail message:
.IP
.EX
uuencode limbo.dis >tmp
.I "place tmp in mail message and send to recipient"
.EE
.PP
Decode the mail message
.RI ( msg
say):
.IP
.EX
uudecode <msg >limbo.dis
.EE
.SH SOURCE
.B /sys/src/cmd/uuencode.c
.br
.B /sys/src/cmd/uudecode.c
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR marshal (1)
.SH BUGS
The encoded file is expanded by at least a third.
.PP
This encoding is a relic of the days before MIME encoding.
